<br>
================================<br>
To go or not to go, that is the question<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 Well, I really can't dodge the realities any longer, its about time I took a long look at my status as regards EverQuest, my guild the Phantom Guard, and this board.<br>
<br>
The truth of the matter is that for all intents and purposes my time in EQ is over unless something drastic happens. Its been a month since I've played and I don't miss the game itself, though I do miss Elhimac and the identity I had created around him and the Guard.<br>
I've played for around a year and a half now and my primary focus in the game has always been roleplaying. <br>
I won't bore you with details of all I've said and done, but sufficient to say that at time of speaking, I have little hope for the organized rping that I was aiming for. <br>
I always knew that my time in EQ would come to and end sometime and frankly I am surprised that its lasted this long.<br>
<br>
The Phantom Guard falls with me, I have no illusions there, and all that remains is really to discuss if my presence on these boards is required. <br>
I have no problem being a moderator even though I don't play the game anymore, but sad to say, I'm quite a bit fustrated that my little corner of the board doesn't see more action than it does and I am wondering if it should be kept up or not.<br>
<br>
Its not that I WANT to go, but I think it is time that I quit dreaming about the impossible and started looking at the realities. <br>
There are so many things I would hate to leave behind, first amongst them is the effort I have put into creating Elhimac's character (not the game character mind you, I'm talking about the identity of him  ) and right behind that is of course the friends I made. <br>
<br>
So my point and question is, should the RP section of this board remain and would you want me to hang around, even if you knew that I would be practically useless ?<br>
I don't post terribly much unless I have something to say, and with my leaving EQ there is not a possibility that I can get events going. (And frankly, I would doubt if I could ever get the attendants that I would like to have for such an event, expirence have shown me as much.)<br>
Note that this is NOT a goodbye post, I'm not gone yet and my account is still clinging like a dwarf  <br>
